14:
What? All we did was buy ourselves 
some groceries.
19:
That was NOT all! Why would you set 
up a magic show in the middle of the 
street?!
20:
And you just HAD to make people 
vanish! I thought that one lady was 
gonna cry after you made her 
husband disappear for THIRTY 
MINUTES.
24:
Hey, hey! Wasn't it funny when you 
pretended not to know me, but then 
I called out your name?
28:
Gee. Touchy today, aren't ya? 
Not getting enough sleep?
32:
That's 'cause YOU keep sneaking into 
my room every night.
34:
Then you leave after chanting some 
weird riddle that keeps me awake FOR 
HOURS ON END.
Why?! Why would you do that to me?!
40:
So? THAT doesn't bother me. Though it 
DOES bother me that it bothers you.
44:
Alk. I don't mean to interrupt your 
siblings' quarrel, but people are 
hungry.
48:
Oh, right!
Also... Siblings?! *shudder* Imagine 
being related to a clown that 
mysteriously makes people vanish.
61:
I mean, I've sure been hanging around 
Alk a lot. We're like fork and spoon, 
peas and carrots, knight and armor! 
You okay with that, Mr. Champion?
65:
It's true that champions and fiends are 
old enemies. But any friend of Alk's is 
a friend of mine.
67:
...Though, I warn you now, betray our 
trust, and you shall pay dearly.
72:
Ooh. Scary monster mask, pal!
Wait, no. That's your real face!
76: You toy with people too much.
79:
Oh phooey. I'm real sorry about that. 
But it's only 'cause I'm so fond of you 
all, Mr. Champion!
86:
Hey! That sunset's really something, 
isn't it?
95:
I've got a riddle for ya. Why would 
a sky with no sun or moon burn red?
98:
Teeheehee! Didjya know we've got no 
luminaries in the skies back home? 
Didjya, didjya?
101:
Not even an itsy-witsy baby twinkle. 
Needless to say, stargazing's not really 
anyone's hobby.
107:
Pandemonium... Is that the name of 
your world?
109:
Folus. Why did the fiends invade my 
land? Why wage a war on humans?
114:
III dunno.
I'm Folus. I'm not like those other 
hawks.
117:
If I were, I wouldn't be here, silly. I'd be 
off, sounding in the bugle in your 
world!
120: Hey! I got another question for ya!
122:
What're you gonna do about the 
fiends, now that ya know we can be 
friendly? Ya gonna keep trying to wipe 
out our armies?
130:
Ah-HAH! It's that gloomy face again! 
Boy oh boy, do I like YOU, Mr. 
Champion!
140:
It's as you say. Perhaps we can end the 
war, and shape a new future for 
mortals and fiends. What would you 
have that future look like?
143:
Gee whiz. That's a big question coming 
out of a small rabbit.
146: Our battle is not over yet.
148:
I hope we both find our answers before 
the end.
153:
What kind of future I want, huh? 
Heeheehee! I'd never even thought 
about that!
